WEBVTT

00:00.187 --> 00:03.122
The Carmichael Show is taped in
front of a live studio audience.

00:03.319 --> 00:05.156
You know, being back
here at my mom's house

00:05.157 --> 00:07.258
brings back a lot of memories.

00:07.259 --> 00:10.428
Most of 'em bad.

00:10.429 --> 00:12.096
But good ones, too.

00:12.097 --> 00:14.265
Like here, I called
this my happy chair.

00:14.266 --> 00:16.100
This the one place in the house

00:16.101 --> 00:17.468
my dad never beat me.

00:19.171 --> 00:22.139
Mm, it is comfy.

00:23.041 --> 00:24.208
You know, I can see why Mom

00:24.209 --> 00:26.343
never wants to come down
to South Carolina with us.

00:26.345 --> 00:28.412
You know there's not a single
picture of her in this house.

00:28.413 --> 00:29.847
Well, I'm sure there's
a picture of your mama

00:29.848 --> 00:31.282
up in here somewhere.

00:31.283 --> 00:32.415
Dad, Grandma has a picture

00:32.417 --> 00:36.287
of you alone on your wedding day.

00:36.288 --> 00:40.424
Well, see, that's because
your mama and your grandmother

00:40.425 --> 00:42.793
always had a very tense relationship.

00:42.794 --> 00:44.462
Yeah, Daddy, why they never got along?

00:44.463 --> 00:47.131
Well, your grandmother always wanted me

00:47.132 --> 00:50.134
to marry a lighter skinned woman.

00:50.135 --> 00:52.136
She tried to like your mama,
but she always thought

00:52.137 --> 00:53.571
she was just a little too dark.

00:54.539 --> 00:56.440
Dad, that's crazy.
I'm sure Grandma doesn't care

00:56.441 --> 00:57.642
what color skin Mom has.

00:57.643 --> 00:58.809
Yes, she does.

00:59.811 --> 01:02.113
See, your grandma came through
a very turbulent time

01:02.114 --> 01:06.150
in history and to her,
lighter skin meant less pain,

01:06.151 --> 01:07.251
less suffering.

01:08.086 --> 01:09.487
She always thought if
I could marry lighter,

01:09.488 --> 01:11.322
that you boys would have a easier time

01:11.323 --> 01:13.290
to make it in the world.

01:13.291 --> 01:18.262
You see, kids, sometimes racism
stems from a place of love.

01:22.668 --> 01:24.835
You know something, Daddy,
I've always said this to myself:

01:24.836 --> 01:27.705
I was just three shades away
from greatness.

01:30.175 --> 01:31.842
There she is.

01:31.843 --> 01:33.811
Aw, look at my boys.

01:33.812 --> 01:36.714
It's like three Snicker
bars came to life.

01:39.484 --> 01:41.519
Was that a comment
about our complexion?

01:41.520 --> 01:42.720
Absolutely.

01:43.588 --> 01:45.656
Okay, gather around.

01:45.657 --> 01:48.359
I got some important news
I need to share with you.

01:48.360 --> 01:50.294
Joe, you might want
to sit down for this.

01:50.295 --> 01:51.862
Mom, what is it? Is everything okay?

01:51.863 --> 01:53.497
Honey, sit down.

01:55.500 --> 01:57.868
Okay, there's no easy way to say this,

01:57.869 --> 01:59.603
so I'm just gonna come
out and tell you.

01:59.604 --> 02:02.606
I've been diagnosed with Alzheimer's.

02:02.607 --> 02:05.342
Wait. That's your news?

02:05.343 --> 02:07.678
Well, I'm sorry to have to
break it to you this way.

02:07.679 --> 02:11.248
Uh, Mom, we've known
about this for six months.

